\[\displaystyle \left|\sum_{k=1}^{2006}x_k\right| ={1\over6}\left|x_{2007}^2-18063\right|.\]Notice that $x_k$ is a multiple of 3 for all $k$, and that $x_k$ and $k$ have the same parity. The requested sum will be a minimum when $|x_{2007}^2-18063|$ is a minimum, that is, when $x_{2007}$ is the multiple of 3 whose square is as close as possible to 18063. Check odd multiples of 3, and find that $129^2<16900$, $141^2>19600$, and $135^2=18225$. The requested minimum is therefore ${1\over6}|135^2-18063|=\boxed{27}$, provided there exists a sequence that satisfies the given conditions and for which $x_{2007}=135$.

An example of such a sequence is
\[x_k= \left\{ \begin{array}{cl}
{3k}& \text{for $k\le45$,}\\
{-138}& \text{for $k>45$ and $k$ even,}\\
{135}& \text{for $k>45$ and $k$ odd.}
\end{array}
\right.\]

data1.problem:
Given that $\overline{MN}\parallel\overline{AB}$, how many units long is $\overline{BN}$?

[asy] pair A,B,M,N,C;
M = 1.2*dir(255); N = dir(285);
A = 3*M; B = 3*N;
draw(M--N--C--A--B--N);
label("A",A,W);label("M",M,W);
label("3",C--M,W);label("5",M--A,W);
label("2.4",C--N,E);label("N",N,E);label("B",B,E);
[/asy]

data1.solution:
First of all, let us label the tip of the triangle. [asy] pair A,B,M,N,C;
M = 1.2*dir(255); N = dir(285);
A = 3*M; B = 3*N;
draw(M--N--C--A--B--N);
label("C",C+(0,0.2));
label("A",A,W);label("M",M,W);
label("3",C--M,W);label("5",M--A,W);
label("2.4",C--N,E);label("N",N,E);label("B",B,E);
[/asy] Since $MN \parallel AB,$ we know that $\angle CMN = \angle CAB$ and $\angle CNM = \angle CBA.$ Therefore, by AA similarity, we have $\triangle ABC \sim MNC.$ Then, we find: \begin{align*}
\frac{AC}{MC} &= \frac{BC}{NC}\\
\frac{AM+MC}{MC} &= \frac{BN+NC}{NC}\\
1 + \frac{AM}{MC} &= 1 + \frac{BN}{NC}\\
\frac{5}{3} &= \frac{BN}{2.4}.
\end{align*} Therefore, $BN = \dfrac{5 \cdot 2.4}{3} = \boxed{4}.$

