merged_question:
How many ways are there for 8 people to sit around a circular table if none of Alice, Bob, and Eve (three of the 8 people) want to sit next to each other? Two seatings are considered the same if one is a rotation of the other. Define $N$ is the number of ways for 8 people to sit around a circular table if none of Alice, Bob, and Eve want to sit next to each other.
 $M$ is 1439 less than $N$.
 The figure shown is called a trefoil and is constructed by drawing circular sectors about sides of the congruent equilateral triangles. What is the area of a trefoil whose horizontal base has length $M$ * 2?
 [asy]
 unitsize(1cm);
 path a =(-1.73,1)..(-1,1.73)--(-2,0)..cycle;
 draw(a,linewidth(0.7));
 path b= (1.73,1)..(2,0)--(1,1.73)..cycle;
 draw(b,linewidth(0.7));
 draw(shift((1,1.73))*a,linewidth(0.7));
 draw(shift((-1,1.73))*b,linewidth(0.7));
 draw((-1,1.73)--(1,1.73)--(0,0)--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
 draw((-2,0)--(2,0),linewidth(0.7));
 draw((-2,-0.2)--(2,-0.2),Arrows);
 label("$M$ * 2",(0,-0.2),S);
 [/asy]

