By the angle bisector theorem, $AC/CD = AB/BD = 105/42 = 5/2$.  Let $AC = 5x$ and $CD = 2x$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.03 cm);

pair A, B, C, D;

A = (0,105);
B = (0,0);
C = (100,0);
D = (42,0);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--D);

